Using 

>> Icarus Verilog version 12.0 (devel) (s20150603-961-g292d174)

Is simple, basic OOP supported? I get the below error for super.new() (Code below). Any clues?

Thanks
Srini

Error:
../ivl_uvm_test_class.sv:13: assert: PFunction.cc:47: failed assertion statement_

```verilog

package test_pkg;

  virtual class uvm_void;
  endclass : uvm_void

  class uvm_object extends uvm_void;
    virtual function void print ();
      $display ("Print");
    endfunction : print 
  endclass : uvm_object

  class uvm_report_object extends uvm_object;
    function new ();
      super.new ();
    endfunction : new 
  endclass : uvm_report_object 

endpackage : test_pkg

module m;
  import test_pkg::*;
  uvm_object u0;
  
   initial begin : test
     #100;
     $display ("Hello World");
     u0 = new ();
     u0.print();

   end : test

endmodule : m

```

